l full of torches as well as some oil flasks.                                                                                                                                                                                                  ÄYou see many of the kings warriors resting.  They are busy eating and restocking any provisions they may need for their patrols.                                                                                                                               —You see the body of Maxwell crumpled on the ground.  His once portly body is now nothing but a skeletal figure.  Draped on his body are his things.  Whatever Maxwell was at one time, it was surely not natural.                                              ûYou see a stout dwarven blacksmith working at an open air forge.  He is mumbling under his breath as he hammers a large section of steel into a breast plate.                                                                                                  ¯He looks up for a moment and says in a gruff tone.  Dwarf: "Me be hating to use but normal steel in me work but there be no Mithril in town to work with.  You fetch me enough mithril to finish these three suits of armor, and I can let you have one.       ;Me be willing to sell you a few items as well if you like."                                                                                                                                                                                                    ¬Dwarf: "Ha!  I see you have some Mithril with ya.  I can work that into some pretty nice armor.  If you let me have it, I can let you have one of these suits of armor as payment."  Do you agree?                                                             hDwarf: "Dat be the best of the three.  Wear it well me friends.  Now I have much work to do.  Good day."                                                                                                                        