ouncil and tell your take of heroics. I am sure they would be most grateful.   ˛Here is a crude map that shall show you the secret way to our city.  You must journey a great distance upon the waters of the "Hells Serpent" and it is a dangerous route.  Remember to mention my name if ever you do journey there."  Flibli bids fare well. ÓYou mention the name Flibli and immediately a crowd gathers.  Crowd: "Flibli!  Did you say Flibli!  Is he OK?  Have you seen him?  What do you know of Flibli?"  You relay your take of having aided him in battle against the Psion-Vampires.                 ÒYour take of heroics quickly spreads through the village.  Apparently Flibli was a most popular fellow.  An elderly gnome speaks to you.  Anju: "My friends.  Flibli was my most favored of divine pupils.  For many years he did tutor under me.              ÌWhen I was asked to choose a representative to journey to Winterhaven, he was the obvious choice.  Flibli is as good natured fellow as you will ever meet.  Your having saved his life means the world to me as it does to the whole village.                  ¯Please accept this gift not from me, but from her most holy 'Feona of Gnalishbin'.  She has always looked out for those of us who devote our lives to her praise.  Now, let her divine goodness look out for you as well."  Anju hands you a small helm.       ?Anju: "May the light of Feona bless you always as she does us."                                                                                                                                                                                                ôA group of Avians is under attack by a larger force of Harpies, Griffins and Cockatrices.  Would you like to aid the Avians in their fight to stay alive?                                                                                                      qThe remaining Avians flee to the skies.  A few however are too wounded to fly.  Do you wish to bind their wounds?               