y dogs even left some of their treasure behind.                                                                                                                                FYou find a small crack in the rubble that has collapsed in the corner.                                                                                                                                                                                         PThe crack widens and you see an ornate casket in a dark secluded chamber beyond.                                                                                                                                                                               ÇYour bodies are thrown about the room like rag dolls.  Great gouts of flame and raw magical energy pelt you from every direction.                                                                                                                              ÚYou clasp your heads in agony as hundreds of voices rush into your brain all at once.  As quickly as they started they stop again.  The cacophony is replaced by a sole voice that speaks in a soothing manner.  Voice: "Who dare disturb my rest.             ÎYou enter the ruins of an old mansion.  At one time it was an impressive dwelling.  Time and decay however have taken their toll.   As if to illustrate the point, the entire northwest section of the first floor appears to be collapsed.                    /You find your equipment stashed in the corner.                                                                                                                                                                                                                 @Who would be so bold as to destroy my pets and invade my house?"                                                                                                                                                                                               —Voice: "I know not of such a thing.  All I do know is that my pets were to guard me so I may rest.  I see now that they were too weak to keep out those such as you.  All I seek is the peace of the afterworld.                                               òI may be able to divine some clues to your search for this "Geyser" of which you speak.  Provided you can do something for me in return.  Do you agree?"                                                                                                       xVoice: "Is that so.  Well, I am sure you will be most welcome to it.  Provided you can evict the current resident.  ME!"                                                                                                                                       ROnce again your head is flooded with the torturous din of a thousand angry voices.                                                                                                                                                                             KYou see but a simple chair and table.  The table is cluttered with potions.                                                                                                                                                                                    'You see three tombs that radiate magic.                                                                                                                                                                                                                        pThis book is cursed!  The pages fly from the book and land all about you.  Each transforms into a hostile beast!                                                                                                                                               µYou marvel at the destructive power of the three cursed books.  You examine them closely and once again they all have their pages as if never read.  Did you wish to read them again?                                                           